Reposition to ownership intelligence layer + new SKU pages

Implements the v2 strategy from AUDIT_AND_UPLIFT.md: away from
"bigger Carsales" toward "Australia's car ownership intelligence
layer" with four surfaces (consumer reports, concierge, dealer SaaS,
partner/API).

Strategy doc:
- AUDIT_AND_UPLIFT.md: full deep audit + repositioning + 90-day
  execution roadmap. Source of truth for v2.

New SKU pages:
- /vehicle-history-report: the $19 killer SKU. Sample report card,
  what's included, comparison vs free PPSR, two CTAs hitting
  /api/reports.
- /concierge: DriveMate buying agent. 5-step explainer, worked
  saving example, MVDA compliance footer.
- /dealer: B2B SaaS landing. Mock Inventory IQ snapshot, floorplan-
  cost proof points, DMS integrations strip, 3-tier pricing,
  14-day no-card trial.

Existing pages updated:
- HeroSection: headline rewritten ("Australia's Ownership
  Intelligence Layer"), subhead repositioned around the four
  surfaces, CTAs point to /vehicle-history-report and /dealer,
  "Trusted by" bar swapped from publisher logos (which awkwardly
  included Carsales) to actual data sources (PPSR, NEVDIS, Pickles,
  Manheim, Dealer Feeds).
- Navigation: nav rewritten around the four surfaces. Header CTA
  now "Get a $19 report".
- pricing/page.tsx: rewritten end-to-end around the four surfaces.
  Honest FAQ.
- README: top-of-file repositioning callout, links to
  AUDIT_AND_UPLIFT.md, new pages listed.
